Pigments on the face are harsh even when its authentic. 
Yes, all controlled in a lab yet still harsh:
Red from rust
Blues from oxidized metals 
Lake dyes are extremely desirable because of strength, stability  and price..but keep in mind its pretty much the same pigments that are used in oil paint..putting that on the face day to day can stress the skin.
Companies like burt bees uses herbal souces for pigments..
Some pigments used in paint like titanium dioxide is also used in food.
If its going on or in the body (baths salts included), its good to read about the sources.
